    <h1>Appetizers</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Caprese Skewers</a></li>
        <p1>Fresh cherry tomatoes, mozzarella balls, and basil leaves are threaded onto skewers and drizzled with a balsamic glaze. Each bite bursts with the flavors of ripe tomatoes, creamy mozzarella, and aromatic basil, complemented by the tangy sweetness of the balsamic reduction.</p1>
        <br>
        <br>
        <li>Stuffed Mushrooms</a></li>
        <p1>Large mushroom caps are filled with a savory mixture of seasoned breadcrumbs, garlic, herbs, and melted cheese, then baked until tender. These bite-sized delights offer a satisfying combination of earthy mushrooms and flavorful stuffing, perfect for any occasion.</p1>
        <br>
        <br>
        <li>Crispy Coconut Shrimps</a></li>
        <p1>Jumbo shrimp are coated in a light and crispy batter made with shredded coconut and panko breadcrumbs, then fried until golden brown. Served with a sweet and tangy dipping sauce, these crunchy shrimp are a tropical-inspired appetizer that's sure to impress with its delightful contrast of textures and flavors.</p1>
        <br>
        <br>
      </ul>
      <hr>

      <h1>Main Courses</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>Grilled Salmon with Lemon Dill Sauce</a></li>
        <p>A fillet of fresh salmon is perfectly grilled to a tender and flaky texture, then topped with a zesty lemon dill sauce. This dish is served with a side of roasted asparagus and garlic mashed potatoes, creating a well-balanced meal that is both light and satisfying, highlighting the natural flavors of the fish complemented by the bright and aromatic sauce.</p>
        <br>
        <li>Beef Wellington</a></li>
        <p>A classic dish featuring a succulent beef tenderloin coated with a rich mushroom duxelles, wrapped in delicate prosciutto and golden puff pastry. Baked to perfection, the beef Wellington is served with a red wine reduction sauce, accompanied by buttery sautéed green beans and a creamy potato gratin, making for an indulgent and impressive centerpiece.</p>
        <br>
        <li>Chicken Alfredo</a></li>
        <p>Tender pieces of grilled chicken breast are served over a bed of fettuccine pasta, smothered in a rich and creamy Alfredo sauce made with Parmesan cheese, butter, and garlic. Garnished with freshly chopped parsley and served with a side of garlic bread, this comforting Italian favorite offers a delightful combination of creamy, cheesy, and savory flavors.</p>
        <br>
        <hr>
      </ul>

      <h1>Desserts</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>Tiramisu</a></li>
        <p>Tiramisu is a classic Italian dessert that consists of layers of coffee-soaked ladyfingers, creamy mascarpone cheese, and a dusting of cocoa powder. This rich and indulgent treat often includes a hint of liqueur such as Marsala or coffee liqueur, adding depth to its flavor profile. The combination of creamy and slightly bitter elements makes it a favorite for many.</p>
        <br>
        <li>Crème Brûlée</a></li>
        <p>Crème Brûlée is a French dessert that features a rich custard base topped with a contrasting layer of hard caramel. The custard is made with cream, eggs, vanilla, and sugar, and it's baked in a water bath to achieve its smooth texture. The caramel topping is created by sprinkling sugar on top and using a torch to caramelize it, resulting in a satisfying crack when tapped with a spoon.</p>
       <br>
        <li>Baklava</a></li>
        <p>Baklava is a Middle Eastern dessert known for its layers of flaky phyllo pastry, chopped nuts, and sweet syrup or honey. The nuts, typically a mixture of walnuts, pistachios, or almonds, are spiced with cinnamon and cloves, creating a rich and aromatic filling. Once baked, the pastry is soaked in a sugar or honey syrup, which seeps into the layers and creates a sweet, sticky treat with a delightful crunch.</p>
<br>
    </ul>
